<p>
Because we are using row-major order, the 2D array is an array of rows.
<pf>numRows</pf> simply returns the length of the rows array.
<pf>numCols</pf> returns the length of the first row, which is the number of columns.
Since the rows all have the same length, we have to check only one.
</p>

<p>
<pf>GridCanvas</pf> also provides a function that gets the <pf>Cell</pf> at a given location, and for convenience when starting the game, a function that turns on the <pf>Cell</pf> at a given location.
